    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "> So far, 3 days after release - main Installing IPython section of http://ipython.org/install.html is useless place to look for 1.0 - Anaconda / EPD (CanopyExpress) still got 0.13.x (ubuntu 0.12x)\n\nThis is the reason of the following message : \n\n```\n...it will take a few days to appear in Anaconda, EPD and Linux distributions.\n```\n\nWe can't do much more.\n\n> Anaconda & Canopy Express might sound quite exotic (compared to all the rest installation options hidden in Docs) for an average Python. Both options weight over 200Mb without prior explanation why\n\n```\nFor new users who want to get up and running with minimal effort,...\n```\n\nSeem like a good explanation to me. Download, run, it works.\nWe had more explanation, and had complaint of the install doc beeing too long and too complicated. \nUser just want it to work.\n\n> There is no clear way to choose Python version beforehand. If user has Python3, he/she gets 2.7 from Anaconda by default.\n\nAnd this is stated in the docs : \n\n```\n... which provide a setup based on Python 2.7\n```\n\nSame as before, asking user to choose 2.x / 3.x is for most already too much and will force us to enter into detail targeted people have no interest in (for this page). \n\n> Despite first line about \"more detailed steps in Documentation\" - there are absolutely nothing (no details) on Anaconda - apt-get in Documentation, which has alternative set of installation methods instead.\n\nFull sentence end with \n\n```\ndetailed instructions for manual **installs** from **source**, targeted at **advanced** users and **developers**.\n```\n\nStill, PR welcomed that could add link to subpages and explanation.\n\nOne could also write heuristics that detect the browser/os/... and provide for custom instruction like [heroku toolbelt](https://toolbelt.heroku.com/) but this is a full time job and lots of maintenance, so it will probably not be done by people in the core (at least not before we have take over a big part of the world).\n"
  },
