    "body": "Just to summarise what Matthias has said at length: there are a bunch of ways to install IPython, and almost all of them suck for one reason or another. The best method depends on your operating system, your level of expertise, what you've already got installed, and what you want to do with it. The installation page has to highlight the easiest options, and resist the temptation to confuse users with alternatives. We know that's not ideal, but it's not a problem we can easily solve.\n"
