    "body": "Hi @2tolik ,\n\nI agree IPython could be much easier to install.  I hope that one day we do have a one click installer; however, for now we do not have the resources to do so.\n\n> We know that's not ideal, but it's not a problem we can easily solve.\n\n:+1: \n\nFor what it's worth, when I install IPython on a new machine I _sort of_ follow this procedure:\n1. Install Python\n2. (optionally) If I remember the dependencies (there are only a handful), I install them first.\n3. Download IPython version (I use git a pull master directly from this repository)\n4. `Python setup.py build` & `Python setup.py install`\n5. Install missing dependencies\n6. Repeat 4 and 5 until no missing dependencies\n"
  },
