    "body": "Thank you guys for polite and details answers. But I'm not the one in need of help. Being relativly new to some systems and tools, still I can manage IPython installation in all possible ways (and verify them along the way :) \n\nI wrote this ticket becase I'm worried that an average person interested in IPython will have difficulties installing IPython 1.0 he/she just heard in news or been wainting for sometime. And just because of old static page, which is \"technically correct\" he/she might got to come through some negative WTFs or simply might be unalbe to get to fascinating IPython world and see what its developers made possible after months of hard work. \n\nSimple as that. I believe there should be straight and obvious ways to get expected results. Agile way - make it working first (up-to-date links and consistent info), and arrange all the details later. \n"
