    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "We agree with you that it's not a great experience for newcomers. But fundamentally, that's not because of our docs, it's because there aren't any good installation options that work well in all cases. `setup.py` won't get you dependencies. `pip` didn't handle binary installers until the very latest version, and it's a faff if people don't already have it installed. Plus if you're installing IPython, there's a good chance you want modules like numpy and matplotlib as well. Anaconda and EPD address all of those issues, and they even work for people who don't already have Python set up.\n\nContinuum and Enthought are probably already aware that there's a new release of IPython - the community communicates effectively. There is a PPA, but Julian, who runs it, is otherwise occupied for a few more days.\n\nFor the sundry changes, like EPD -> Canopy, feel free to open a pull request. You can find the source file here: https://github.com/ipython/ipython-website/blob/master/install.rst\n"
  },
